  "text": "Cyclic AMP. ACTH-induced cAMP was determined in three PCa cell lines. Briefly, PC3, DU-145, and LNCaP cells were plated in 6-well plates and allowed to attach for 16 h. The following day, the cells were washed twice with warm Waymouth/BSA. Then fresh Waymouth/BSA containing 0.5 mM isobutylmethylxanthine (IBMX) (a cAMP promoter Fig. 7 . Intracellular cAMP was extracted using 0.5 N perchloric acid containing 180 µg/ml theophylline (Sigma), and measured using radioimmunoassay [CITATION_1] . All determinations were performed in triplicate. The cAMP levels were calculated as fold increase over basal levels of each cell line. Maximal response (Rmax) and EC 50 values were calculated with GraphPad software.",
